story.storyDescription: The future isn't quite what Jeff and Tonya thought it would be...
story.title: Frontier: Earth - Episode 1

messages.text: I‚Äôm‚Ä¶here.
OMG, you made it?!
You‚Äôre in the future?
I don‚Äôt know for sure. Something feels‚Ä¶off.
What‚Äôs wrong? The time machine worked, right?
I‚Äôm not sure‚Ä¶
We set it for one million years **ahead** right?
Yeah‚Ä¶why? What do you see?
Is it a gleaming mega-city with flying space cars and robots?
No. It‚Äôs‚Ä¶overgrown.
There‚Äôs jungle everywhere.
I don‚Äôt get it ‚Äî I really didn‚Äôt expect that.
Me neither. There‚Äôs no city here‚Ä¶
No CIVILIZATION at all.
It‚Äôs also really, REALLY hot, Tonya ‚Äî so hot for January.
The air is heavy and dense.
You don't think‚Ä¶
What if you accidentally went backward in time?
Yeah, that‚Äôs what I‚Äôm worried about‚Ä¶
It would make more sense, given what I'm seeing.
Let me investigate.
I‚Äôm so sorry ‚Äî I didn‚Äôt mean to send you into the past!
Does this mean you‚Äôre a million years back?
Idk. But it‚Äôs not your fault‚Äî
We calibrated the machine together.
And it's not a perfect science yet.
What're you doing now?
I‚Äôm making my way down to the ocean.
There are no people AT ALL. It feels really weird‚Ä¶
Yeah, well, that‚Äôs how it was one million years ago üôÅ
WOAH!
What is it?
I just saw a‚Ä¶DINOSAUR.
OMG! Well, that confirms it ‚Äî you definitely are in the past.
It came out of the jungle about 100 yards up the beach.
What kind of dinosaur is it?!
I‚Äôm not sure. It looks like a giant lizard ‚Äî it‚Äôs gotta be the size of a small car.
That doesn‚Äôt sound good‚Ä¶
I‚Äôm bringing you back here, Jeff ‚Äî now!
No, wait. I have my gun with me. Remember?
Isn‚Äôt it only a .38 pistol?
Will that be able to stop a DINOSAUR!?
Woah‚Ä¶wait, there ARE people here!
What? In the past?
Yeah. The dinosaur stuck its head in this cave. Then PEOPLE came running out!
That‚Äôs weird‚Ä¶
Oh no!
What?
The dinosaur is chasing the people!
It‚Äôs trying to kill them but they only have spears and rocks.
Oh god ‚Äî it just caught a woman with its tongue!
Tonya, the woman had a baby in her arms, but it flew out‚Äî
Now it‚Äôs crawling away on the beach‚Ä¶
Shoot the dinosaur, Jeff! Kill it!!
I don‚Äôt know if I can‚Ä¶
I‚Äôm in the past, right? So if I interfere and kill something‚Ä¶
Won‚Äôt that alter the future?
Could it affect you?
God, I don‚Äôt know! But what about the baby?!
I‚Äôm running closer to help it.
Oh, gross‚Äî the dinosaur has officially eaten the woman. It‚Äôs disgusting‚Ä¶
Jeff, focus. Where‚Äôs the baby?
Still on the beach. Oh wait‚Äî
Shoot! The dinosaur is moving towards it!
Kill it, Jeff! You have to save the baby!!
I don‚Äôt know! I can‚Äôt interfere‚Ä¶
It‚Äôs a HUMAN baby, Jeff!
Jeff‚Ä¶what‚Äôs happening?
I shot it five times in the head and killed it.
I can‚Äôt believe I killed a DINOSAUR.
What about the baby?
It‚Äôs safe ‚Äî one of the women picked it up.
All the people are retreating back to their cave‚Ä¶
You‚Äôre a hero!
I feel more like a traitor to science.
Has anything changed in your present?
Nope. Not a thing.
I‚Äôm looking out the window now. Same buildings and same cars and same people.
Thank GOD.
Uh-oh‚Ä¶a man just came out of the cave. A BIG MAN.
You still have bullets?
Yes.
He‚Äôs looking at the dead dinosaur. He‚Äôs looking at me‚Ä¶
Careful‚Ä¶
Tonya, this guy is HUGE‚Ä¶
Jeff‚Ä¶this whole thing is weird‚Ä¶
Because dinosaurs and humans never existed together in the past, right?
Dinosaurs went extinct 65 MILLION YEARS ago.
And humans didn‚Äôt appear until 250,000 YEARS ago‚Ä¶
I know.
So WHAT is going on over there??
I wish I knew‚Ä¶
Now the caveman is kneeling in the sand‚Ä¶
He‚Äôs like 10 feet away from me‚Ä¶
And he‚Äôs holding something out to me‚Ä¶
What is it?!
I can‚Äôt tell from over here‚Ä¶but I think he wants me to take it?
Maybe he‚Äôs giving you a gift for saving his people!
Okay, I took it. And he ran back to his cave.
What is it?
It‚Äôs a small leather pouch. There‚Äôs something inside‚Ä¶
It‚Äôs a coin.
Woah‚Ä¶it‚Äôs made out of pure DIAMOND.
OMG!!
What?!
The coin has an eagle on one side that says USA MINT.
Could I seriously be in America??
OMG, maybe‚Ä¶is there anything on the other side of the coin?
Yeah. There's a date.
What?! What does it say?
OMG!! Then you DID go into the future.
Yeah. I must‚Äôve gone‚Ä¶one million years‚Ä¶into the‚Ä¶future.
The machine DID work!
This is nuts.
Civilization is all‚Ä¶gone.
And the dinosaurs are back. And cavemen, too?
I‚Äôm coming there!
What?! No!
Why would you want to do that?
I almost died out here‚Äî
Tonya, there are DINOSAURS.
So? I'll bring another pistol and two rifles.
And lots of ammunition‚Ä¶
But why?!
You know the time machine is only good for two trips‚Äî
And I‚Äôve already used one!
You‚Äôve got to bring me home with the last one.
No way. Don‚Äôt you see?
We can help these people!
We can help them fight the dinosaurs!
Humans might go extinct without us.
I don‚Äôt think that‚Äôs the best way to do it.
But we don‚Äôt like our life in the present‚Äî
That‚Äôs why we built the time machine in the first place.
Tonya, I‚Äôm not kidding. Bring me home.
We‚Äôll fix the time machine together‚Äî
We can set it for more trips next time.
Oh God‚Ä¶please Tonya, you have to listen to me‚Äî
The ground is shaking.
OMG, the ground is shaking and I don‚Äôt know what it is.
Are you even telling me the truth right now?
Yes ‚Äî Tonya, I see it!
The reason the ground was shaking ‚Äî there‚Äôs a giant Tyrannosaurus Rex!
OH GOD! It‚Äôs coming up right toward me‚Äî
Please ‚Äî please bring me back!
Okay, I got you. Just a second‚Ä¶
NOW, Tonya.
I‚Äôm plugging in the code‚Ä¶
He‚Äôs gaining on me. Hurry!
As the T Rex tears at the hood of Jeff‚Äôs jacket with his sharp claws‚Ä¶
Jeff hears a humming noise in his ears ‚Äî followed by a loud pop, like a suction.
In the next moment, he finds himself back in the lab, sitting next to Tonya.
She smiles at him and reaches out to rub his back.
You weren‚Äôt kidding. Your jacket‚Äôs all torn.
Tonya, I‚Äôd never lie to you.
Next time, you‚Äôre gonna be the one to see it.
Then I better load my guns.
The future‚Äôs a dangerous frontier.
